```class Solution {
    public int appendCharacters(String s, String t) {
        int i = s.length() - 1, j = t.length() - 1;
        while (i >= 0 && j >= 0) {
            if (s.charAt(i) == t.charAt(j)) {
                j--;
            }
            i--;
        }
        return t.length() - j - 1;
    }
}```
efficiency: HIGH
time complexity: O(m + n)
space complexity: O(1)
energy implications: LOW
explanation: We use two pointers, one for each string, to iterate from the end towards the beginning. We compare characters at the current positions and move the pointer of the string with the smaller character. The remaining characters in the second string are the ones that need to be appended to the end of the first string.

